## cp3 — the validation engine (the hard one), done right
- Strict date parsing per dateFormat (05/06 under DD/MM = 5 June, not
  6 May; invalid dates = bad rows, no silent coercion)
- Both dedups: in-file (2nd occurrence points at 1st) + external (one
  batched findMany vs roster)
- Row-numbering matches Excel (header=0, data=1, blanks hold slot but
  uncounted) — error report is admin-actionable
- Retryable-vs-fatal taxonomy (UnrecoverableError fails fast, transient
  retries 3x)
- Proven against an 11-row messy fixture: 4 good / 5 bad, correct row
  numbers + messages. CI-verified.

